CROP PREDICTION MODEL

In [ ]:
x = crop_data[['N','P', 'K']]
y = crop_data[['humidity', 'ph']]
In [ ]:
x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=50)
In [ ]:
#standardizing or normalizing the features
scaler = StandardScaler()
x_train = scaler.fit_transform(x_train)
x_test = scaler.transform(x_test)
In [ ]:
#Training the model
model = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=50)
model.fit(x_train, y_train)

WATER REQUIREMENT ANALYSIS

In [ ]:
# Get user input for land area (in square meters) and moisture level (in percentage)
land_area = float(input("Enter the land area for the desired crop (in square meters): "))
moisture_level = float(input("Enter the moisture level in the crop area (in percentage): "))

# Calculate the amount of water present (in liters)
water_present = (land_area * moisture_level) / 100

# Display the result
print(f"The amount of water present in the crop area in this case is {water_present:.2f} liters.")
